            <event type="researchStep">
               <head xml:lang="en">Build the model of the dictionary</head>
               <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en">The first step is to identify the structural
                  components of the dictionary and test if they can be represented in TEI. Some
                  steps to consider may be: <list>
                     <item>Identify the apporpriate language code (ideally BCP 47) for the
                        linguistic varieties involved in the dictionary project</item>
                     <item>Check the TEI guidelines (section 9, Dictionaries)</item>
                     <item>For existing dictionaries, try to find one example for all possible
                        variants of the entry.</item>
                     <item>Experiment with an XML editor (like Oxygen) and a TEI schema.</item>
                  </list>
               </desc>
               <desc type="term" xml:lang="en">
